phione.name: Phione
phione.description: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.

manaphy.name: Manaphy
manaphy.description: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

darkrai.name: Darkrai
darkrai.description: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

shaymin.name: Shaymin
shaymin.description: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.

arceus.name: Arceus
arceus.description: It is described in mythology as the Pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.

victini.name: Victini
victini.description: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

snivy.name: Snivy
snivy.description: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.

servine.name: Servine
servine.description: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

serperior.name: Serperior
serperior.description: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

tepig.name: Tepig
tepig.description: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

pignite.name: Pignite
pignite.description: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

emboar.name: Emboar
emboar.description: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

oshawott.name: Oshawott
oshawott.description: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

dewott.name: Dewott
dewott.description: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

samurott.name: Samurott
samurott.description: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

patrat.name: Patrat
patrat.description: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

watchog.name: Watchog
watchog.description: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

lillipup.name: Lillipup
lillipup.description: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokémon flees.

herdier.name: Herdier
herdier.description: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

stoutland.name: Stoutland
stoutland.description: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

purrloin.name: Purrloin
purrloin.description: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

liepard.name: Liepard
liepard.description: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

pansage.name: Pansage
pansage.description: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

simisage.name: Simisage
simisage.description: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

pansear.name: Pansear
pansear.description: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.

simisear.name: Simisear
simisear.description: It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.

panpour.name: Panpour
panpour.description: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

simipour.name: Simipour
simipour.description: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.

munna.name: Munna
munna.description: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.

musharna.name: Musharna
musharna.description: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.

pidove.name: Pidove
pidove.description: Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

tranquill.name: Tranquill
tranquill.description: It can return to its Trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.

unfezant.name: Unfezant
unfezant.description: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.

blitzle.name: Blitzle
blitzle.description: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.

zebstrika.name: Zebstrika
zebstrika.description: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

roggenrola.name: Roggenrola
roggenrola.description: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.

boldore.name: Boldore
boldore.description: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

gigalith.name: Gigalith
gigalith.description: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

woobat.name: Woobat
woobat.description: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

swoobat.name: Swoobat
swoobat.description: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

drilbur.name: Drilbur
drilbur.description: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

excadrill.name: Excadrill
excadrill.description: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.

audino.name: Audino
audino.description: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

timburr.name: Timburr
timburr.description: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

gurdurr.name: Gurdurr
gurdurr.description: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

conkeldurr.name: Conkeldurr
conkeldurr.description: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.

tympole.name: Tympole
tympole.description: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.

palpitoad.name: Palpitoad
palpitoad.description: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

seismitoad.name: Seismitoad
seismitoad.description: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

throh.name: Throh
throh.description: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

sawk.name: Sawk
sawk.description: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.

sewaddle.name: Sewaddle
sewaddle.description: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

swadloon.name: Swadloon
swadloon.description: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

leavanny.name: Leavanny
leavanny.description: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

venipede.name: Venipede
venipede.description: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

whirlipede.name: Whirlipede
whirlipede.description: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

scolipede.name: Scolipede
scolipede.description: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

cottonee.name: Cottonee
cottonee.description: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

whimsicott.name: Whimsicott
whimsicott.description: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

petilil.name: Petilil
petilil.description: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

lilligant.name: Lilligant
lilligant.description: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

basculin.name: Basculin
basculin.description: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they’ll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile.

sandile.name: Sandile
sandile.description: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

krokorok.name: Krokorok
krokorok.description: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

krookodile.name: Krookodile
krookodile.description: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

darumaka.name: Darumaka
darumaka.description: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

darmanitan.name: Darmanitan
darmanitan.description: Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

maractus.name: Maractus
maractus.description: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

dwebble.name: Dwebble
dwebble.description: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

crustle.name: Crustle
crustle.description: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

scraggy.name: Scraggy
scraggy.description: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

scrafty.name: Scrafty
scrafty.description: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

sigilyph.name: Sigilyph
sigilyph.description: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

yamask.name: Yamask
yamask.description: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

cofagrigus.name: Cofagrigus
cofagrigus.description: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

tirtouga.name: Tirtouga
tirtouga.description: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

carracosta.name: Carracosta
carracosta.description: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

archen.name: Archen
archen.description: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

archeops.name: Archeops
archeops.description: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

trubbish.name: Trubbish
trubbish.description: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

garbodor.name: Garbodor
garbodor.description: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

zorua.name: Zorua
zorua.description: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

zoroark.name: Zoroark
zoroark.description: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

minccino.name: Minccino
minccino.description: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

cinccino.name: Cinccino
cinccino.description: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

gothita.name: Gothita
gothita.description: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

gothorita.name: Gothorita
gothorita.description: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

gothitelle.name: Gothitelle
gothitelle.description: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

solosis.name: Solosis
solosis.description: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

duosion.name: Duosion
duosion.description: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

reuniclus.name: Reuniclus
reuniclus.description: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

ducklett.name: Ducklett
ducklett.description: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

swanna.name: Swanna
swanna.description: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

vanillite.name: Vanillite
vanillite.description: The temperature of their breath is -58° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

vanillish.name: Vanillish
vanillish.description: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon’s habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

vanilluxe.name: Vanilluxe
vanilluxe.description: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

deerling.name: Deerling
deerling.description: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

sawsbuck.name: Sawsbuck
sawsbuck.description: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.

emolga.name: Emolga
emolga.description: The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

karrablast.name: Karrablast
karrablast.description: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

escavalier.name: Escavalier
escavalier.description: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

foongus.name: Foongus
foongus.description: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

amoonguss.name: Amoonguss
amoonguss.description: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

frillish.name: Frillish
frillish.description: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

jellicent.name: Jellicent
jellicent.description: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent’s habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

alomomola.name: Alomomola
alomomola.description: The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.

joltik.name: Joltik
joltik.description: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

galvantula.name: Galvantula
galvantula.description: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

ferroseed.name: Ferroseed
ferroseed.description: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

ferrothorn.name: Ferrothorn
ferrothorn.description: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

klink.name: Klink
klink.description: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

klang.name: Klang
klang.description: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

klinklang.name: Klinklang
klinklang.description: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

tynamo.name: Tynamo
tynamo.description: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

eelektrik.name: Eelektrik
eelektrik.description: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

eelektross.name: Eelektross
eelektross.description: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

elgyem.name: Elgyem
elgyem.description: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.

beheeyem.name: Beheeyem
beheeyem.description: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

litwick.name: Litwick
litwick.description: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

lampent.name: Lampent
lampent.description: This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

chandelure.name: Chandelure
chandelure.description: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

axew.name: Axew
axew.description: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

fraxure.name: Fraxure
fraxure.description: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.

haxorus.name: Haxorus
haxorus.description: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

cubchoo.name: Cubchoo
cubchoo.description: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.

beartic.name: Beartic
beartic.description: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

cryogonal.name: Cryogonal
cryogonal.description: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

shelmet.name: Shelmet
shelmet.description: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.

accelgor.name: Accelgor
accelgor.description: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

stunfisk.name: Stunfisk
stunfisk.description: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

mienfoo.name: Mienfoo
mienfoo.description: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

mienshao.name: Mienshao
mienshao.description: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

druddigon.name: Druddigon
druddigon.description: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

golett.name: Golett
golett.description: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

golurk.name: Golurk
golurk.description: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

pawniard.name: Pawniard
pawniard.description: Blades comprise this Pokémon’s entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

bisharp.name: Bisharp
bisharp.description: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.

bouffalant.name: Bouffalant
bouffalant.description: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

rufflet.name: Rufflet
rufflet.description: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

braviary.name: Braviary
braviary.description: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

vullaby.name: Vullaby
vullaby.description: Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the time approaches for it to evolve, it discards the bones it was wearing.

mandibuzz.name: Mandibuzz
mandibuzz.description: It makes a nest out of bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.

heatmor.name: Heatmor
heatmor.description: It breathes through a hole in its tail while it burns with an internal fire. Durant is its prey.

durant.name: Durant
durant.description: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

deino.name: Deino
deino.description: It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.

zweilous.name: Zweilous
zweilous.description: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

hydreigon.name: Hydreigon
hydreigon.description: This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.

larvesta.name: Larvesta
larvesta.description: This Pokémon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.

volcarona.name: Volcarona
volcarona.description: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona’s fire provided a replacement for the sun.

cobalion.name: Cobalion
cobalion.description: This legendary Pokémon battled against humans to protect Pokémon. Its personality is calm and composed.

terrakion.name: Terrakion
terrakion.description: This Pokémon came to the defense of Pokémon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.

virizion.name: Virizion
virizion.description: This Pokémon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.

tornadus.name: Tornadus
tornadus.description: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

thundurus.name: Thundurus
thundurus.description: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.

reshiram.name: Reshiram
reshiram.description: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

zekrom.name: Zekrom
zekrom.description: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

landorus.name: Landorus
landorus.description: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

kyurem.name: Kyurem
kyurem.description: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

keldeo.name: Keldeo
keldeo.description: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.

meloetta.name: Meloetta
meloetta.description: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

genesect.name: Genesect
genesect.description: Over 300 million years ago, it was feared as the strongest of hunters. It has been modified by Team Plasma.

chespin.name: Chespin
chespin.description: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

quilladin.name: Quilladin
quilladin.description: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators’ attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

chesnaught.name: Chesnaught
chesnaught.description: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

fennekin.name: Fennekin
fennekin.description: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

braixen.name: Braixen
braixen.description: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

delphox.name: Delphox
delphox.description: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

froakie.name: Froakie
froakie.description: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

frogadier.name: Frogadier
frogadier.description: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

greninja.name: Greninja
greninja.description: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

bunnelby.name: Bunnelby
bunnelby.description: They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.

diggersby.name: Diggersby
diggersby.description: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.

fletchling.name: Fletchling
fletchling.description: These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.

fletchinder.name: Fletchinder
fletchinder.description: From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.

talonflame.name: Talonflame
talonflame.description: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.

scatterbug.name: Scatterbug
scatterbug.description: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

spewpa.name: Spewpa
spewpa.description: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

vivillon.name: Vivillon
vivillon.description: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.

litleo.name: Litleo
litleo.description: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.

pyroar.name: Pyroar
pyroar.description: The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.

flabebe.name: Flabébé
flabebe.description: It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower Flabébé holds is most likely part of its body.

floette.name: Floette
floette.description: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.

florges.name: Florges
florges.description: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.

skiddo.name: Skiddo
skiddo.description: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

gogoat.name: Gogoat
gogoat.description: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

pancham.name: Pancham
pancham.description: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.

pangoro.name: Pangoro
pangoro.description: Although it possesses a violent temperament, it won’t put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.

furfrou.name: Furfrou
furfrou.description: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.

espurr.name: Espurr
espurr.description: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.

meowstic.name: Meowstic
meowstic.description: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.

honedge.name: Honedge
honedge.description: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

doublade.name: Doublade
doublade.description: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.

aegislash.name: Aegislash
aegislash.description: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.

spritzee.name: Spritzee
spritzee.description: It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.

aromatisse.name: Aromatisse
aromatisse.description: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.

swirlix.name: Swirlix
swirlix.description: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.

slurpuff.name: Slurpuff
slurpuff.description: It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.

inkay.name: Inkay
inkay.description: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

malamar.name: Malamar
malamar.description: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.

binacle.name: Binacle
binacle.description: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.

barbaracle.name: Barbaracle
barbaracle.description: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.

skrelp.name: Skrelp
skrelp.description: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.

dragalge.name: Dragalge
dragalge.description: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.

clauncher.name: Clauncher
clauncher.description: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.

clawitzer.name: Clawitzer
clawitzer.description: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

helioptile.name: Helioptile
helioptile.description: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

heliolisk.name: Heliolisk
heliolisk.description: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.

tyrunt.name: Tyrunt
tyrunt.description: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn’t like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.

tyrantrum.name: Tyrantrum
tyrantrum.description: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.

amaura.name: Amaura
amaura.description: This ancient Pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.

aurorus.name: Aurorus
aurorus.description: The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.

sylveon.name: Sylveon
sylveon.description: It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.

hawlucha.name: Hawlucha
hawlucha.description: Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.

dedenne.name: Dedenne
dedenne.description: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.

carbink.name: Carbink
carbink.description: Born from the temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.

goomy.name: Goomy
goomy.description: The weakest Dragon-type Pokémon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn’t dry out.

sliggoo.name: Sliggoo
sliggoo.description: It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can’t see anything.

goodra.name: Goodra
goodra.description: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokémon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.

klefki.name: Klefki
klefki.description: These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.

phantump.name: Phantump
phantump.description: These Pokémon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.

trevenant.name: Trevenant
trevenant.description: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.

pumpkaboo.name: Pumpkaboo
pumpkaboo.description: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

gourgeist.name: Gourgeist
gourgeist.description: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.

bergmite.name: Bergmite
bergmite.description: It blocks opponents’ attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.

avalugg.name: Avalugg
avalugg.description: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.

noibat.name: Noibat
noibat.description: They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.

noivern.name: Noivern
noivern.description: They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.

xerneas.name: Xerneas
xerneas.description: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

yveltal.name: Yveltal
yveltal.description: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

zygarde.name: Zygarde
zygarde.description: When the Kalos region’s ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.

diancie.name: Diancie
diancie.description: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

hoopa.name: Hoopa
hoopa.description: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.

volcanion.name: Volcanion
volcanion.description: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.

rowlet.name: Rowlet
rowlet.description: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

dartrix.name: Dartrix
dartrix.description: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

decidueye.name: Decidueye
decidueye.description: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.

litten.name: Litten
litten.description: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

torracat.name: Torracat
torracat.description: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.

incineroar.name: Incineroar
incineroar.description: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it’s not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer’s orders with complete nonchalance.

popplio.name: Popplio
popplio.description: This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It’s famous for being a hard worker.

brionne.name: Brionne
brionne.description: A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, and briskly bombards its enemies.

primarina.name: Primarina
primarina.description: It controls its water balloons with song. The melody is learned from others of its kind and is passed down from one generation to the next.

pikipek.name: Pikipek
pikipek.description: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food storage and for nesting.

trumbeak.name: Trumbeak
trumbeak.description: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.

toucannon.name: Toucannon
toucannon.description: When it battles, its beak heats up. The temperature can easily exceed 212 degrees Fahrenheit, causing severe burns when it hits.

yungoos.name: Yungoos
yungoos.description: With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.

gumshoos.name: Gumshoos
gumshoos.description: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location...but it’s always snoozing by nightfall.

grubbin.name: Grubbin
grubbin.description: Its strong jaw enables it to scrape trees and slurp out the sap. It normally lives underground.

charjabug.name: Charjabug
charjabug.description: Its body is capable of storing electricity. On camping trips, people are grateful to have one around.

vikavolt.name: Vikavolt
vikavolt.description: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.

crabrawler.name: Crabrawler
crabrawler.description: While guarding its weak points with its pincers, it looks for an opening and unleashes punches. When it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.

crabominable.name: Crabominable
crabominable.description: It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this Pokémon evolved and grew fur.

oricorio.name: Oricorio
oricorio.description: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.

cutiefly.name: Cutiefly
cutiefly.description: It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it’s able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.

ribombee.name: Ribombee
ribombee.description: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.

rockruff.name: Rockruff
rockruff.description: It’s considered to be a good Pokémon for beginners because of its friendliness, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.

lycanroc.name: Lycanroc
lycanroc.description: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.

wishiwashi.name: Wishiwashi
wishiwashi.description: When it’s in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.

mareanie.name: Mareanie
mareanie.description: It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.

toxapex.name: Toxapex
toxapex.description: Toxapex crawls along the ocean floor on its 12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits scattered in its wake.

mudbray.name: Mudbray
mudbray.description: The mud stuck to Mudbray’s hooves enhances its grip and its powerful running gait.

mudsdale.name: Mudsdale
mudsdale.description: It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.

dewpider.name: Dewpider
dewpider.description: It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.

araquanid.name: Araquanid
araquanid.description: It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokémon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.

fomantis.name: Fomantis
fomantis.description: During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light. When night falls, it walks around looking for a safer place to sleep.

lurantis.name: Lurantis
lurantis.description: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis’s vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.

morelull.name: Morelull
morelull.description: It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.

shiinotic.name: Shiinotic
shiinotic.description: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People confused by its strange lights can never find their way home again.

salandit.name: Salandit
salandit.description: It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.

salazzle.name: Salazzle
salazzle.description: For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.

stufful.name: Stufful
stufful.description: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.

bewear.name: Bewear
bewear.description: This immensely dangerous Pokémon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.

bounsweet.name: Bounsweet
bounsweet.description: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by Toucannon lured by that wafting deliciousness.

steenee.name: Steenee
steenee.description: The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.

tsareena.name: Tsareena
tsareena.description: Its long, striking legs aren’t just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.

comfey.name: Comfey
comfey.description: It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. This revitalizes the flowers, and they give off an aromatic scent.

oranguru.name: Oranguru
oranguru.description: Known for its extreme intelligence, this Pokémon will look down on inexperienced Trainers, so it’s best suited to veteran Trainers.

passimian.name: Passimian
passimian.description: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.

wimpod.name: Wimpod
wimpod.description: This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.

golisopod.name: Golisopod
golisopod.description: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.

sandygast.name: Sandygast
sandygast.description: Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this Pokémon embodies the grudges of the departed.

palossand.name: Palossand
palossand.description: Possessed people controlled by this Pokémon transformed its sand mound into a castle. As it evolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.

pyukumuku.name: Pyukumuku
pyukumuku.description: It lives in shallow seas, such as areas near a beach. It can eject its internal organs, which it uses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.

typenull.name: Type: Null
typenull.description: Rumor has it that the theft of top-secret research notes led to a new instance of this Pokémon being created in the Galar region.

silvally.name: Silvally
silvally.description: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokémon is capable of changing its type, a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.

minior.name: Minior
minior.description: Originally making its home in the ozone layer, it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosing its body grows too heavy.

komala.name: Komala
komala.description: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.

turtonator.name: Turtonator
turtonator.description: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.

togedemaru.name: Togedemaru
togedemaru.description: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokémon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.

mimikyu.name: Mimikyu
mimikyu.description: After going to all the effort of disguising itself, its neck was broken. Whatever is inside is probably unharmed, but it’s still feeling sad.

bruxish.name: Bruxish
bruxish.description: When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the grating sound of grinding teeth echoes through the area.

drampa.name: Drampa
drampa.description: It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it completely destroys its surroundings with its intense breath.

dhelmise.name: Dhelmise
dhelmise.description: Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord in a single blow. What appears to be green seaweed is actually its body.

jangmoo.name: Jangmo-o
jangmoo.description: They learn to fight by smashing their head scales together. The dueling strengthens both their skills and their spirits.

hakamoo.name: Hakamo-o
hakamoo.description: The scaleless, scarred parts of its body are signs of its strength. It shows them off to defeated opponents.

kommoo.name: Kommo-o
kommoo.description: It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents. This Pokémon will battle only those who stand steadfast in the face of this display.

tapukoko.name: Tapu Koko
tapukoko.description: Although it’s called a guardian deity, if a person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood, it will become a malevolent deity and attack.

tapulele.name: Tapu Lele
tapulele.description: It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales. This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

tapubulu.name: Tapu Bulu
tapubulu.description: Although it’s called a guardian deity, it’s violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

tapufini.name: Tapu Fini
tapufini.description: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.

cosmog.name: Cosmog
cosmog.description: Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.

cosmoem.name: Cosmoem
cosmoem.description: Motionless as if dead, its body is faintly warm to the touch. In the distant past, it was called the cocoon of the stars.

solgaleo.name: Solgaleo
solgaleo.description: It is said to live in another world. The intense light it radiates from the surface of its body can make the darkest of nights light up like midday.

lunala.name: Lunala
lunala.description: It is said to be a female evolution of Cosmog. When its third eye activates, away it flies to another world.

nihilego.name: Nihilego
nihilego.description: One of several mysterious Ultra Beasts. People on the street report observing those infested by it suddenly becoming violent.

buzzwole.name: Buzzwole
buzzwole.description: This Ultra Beast appeared from another world. It shows off its body, but whether that display is a boast or a threat remains unclear.

pheromosa.name: Pheromosa
pheromosa.description: One of the dangerous Ultra Beasts, it has been spotted running across the land at terrific speeds.

xurkitree.name: Xurkitree
xurkitree.description: One of the mysterious life-forms known as Ultra Beasts. Astonishing electric shocks emanate from its entire body, according to witnesses.

celesteela.name: Celesteela
celesteela.description: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. Witnesses observed it flying across the sky at high speed.

kartana.name: Kartana
kartana.description: This Ultra Beast came from the Ultra Wormhole. It seems not to attack enemies on its own, but its sharp body is a dangerous weapon in itself.

guzzlord.name: Guzzlord
guzzlord.description: It has gobbled mountains and swallowed whole buildings, according to reports. It’s one of the Ultra Beasts.

necrozma.name: Necrozma
necrozma.description: Reminiscent of the Ultra Beasts, this life-form, apparently asleep underground, is thought to have come from another world in ancient times.

magearna.name: Magearna
magearna.description: This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.

marshadow.name: Marshadow
marshadow.description: Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before humans, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.

poipole.name: Poipole
poipole.description: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.

naganadel.name: Naganadel
naganadel.description: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

stakataka.name: Stakataka
stakataka.description: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

blacephalon.name: Blacephalon
blacephalon.description: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

zeraora.name: Zeraora
zeraora.description: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

meltan.name: Meltan
meltan.description: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

melmetal.name: Melmetal
melmetal.description: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.

grookey.name: Grookey
grookey.description: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

thwackey.name: Thwackey
thwackey.description: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.

rillaboom.name: Rillaboom
rillaboom.description: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

scorbunny.name: Scorbunny
scorbunny.description: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon’s body. Once that happens, it’s ready to fight at full power.

raboot.name: Raboot
raboot.description: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves.

cinderace.name: Cinderace
cinderace.description: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.

sobble.name: Sobble
sobble.description: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won’t be able to resist weeping.

drizzile.name: Drizzile
drizzile.description: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.

inteleon.name: Inteleon
inteleon.description: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

skwovet.name: Skwovet
skwovet.description: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.

greedent.name: Greedent
greedent.description: It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn’t notice the loss.

rookidee.name: Rookidee
rookidee.description: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.

corvisquire.name: Corvisquire
corvisquire.description: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.

corviknight.name: Corviknight
corviknight.description: This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.

blipbug.name: Blipbug
blipbug.description: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn’t.

dottler.name: Dottler
dottler.description: It barely moves, but it’s still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.

orbeetle.name: Orbeetle
orbeetle.description: It’s famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.

nickit.name: Nickit
nickit.description: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.

thievul.name: Thievul
thievul.description: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.

gossifleur.name: Gossifleur
gossifleur.description: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

eldegoss.name: Eldegoss
eldegoss.description: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

wooloo.name: Wooloo
wooloo.description: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

dubwool.name: Dubwool
dubwool.description: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You’ll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

chewtle.name: Chewtle
chewtle.description: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.

drednaw.name: Drednaw
drednaw.description: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

yamper.name: Yamper
yamper.description: This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.

boltund.name: Boltund
boltund.description: This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.

rolycoly.name: Rolycoly
rolycoly.description: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.

carkol.name: Carkol
carkol.description: It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.

coalossal.name: Coalossal
coalossal.description: It’s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

applin.name: Applin
applin.description: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it’s just an apple and nothing more.

flapple.name: Flapple
flapple.description: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.

appletun.name: Appletun
appletun.description: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.

silicobra.name: Silicobra
silicobra.description: As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold more than 17 pounds of sand.

sandaconda.name: Sandaconda
sandaconda.description: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.

cramorant.name: Cramorant
cramorant.description: It’s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it’s battling midfight.

arrokuda.name: Arrokuda
arrokuda.description: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It’s very proud of that jaw.

barraskewda.name: Barraskewda
barraskewda.description: This Pokémon has a jaw that’s as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda’s flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.

toxel.name: Toxel
toxel.description: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.

toxtricity.name: Toxtricity
toxtricity.description: Capable of generating 15,000 volts of electricity, this Pokémon looks down on all that would challenge it.

sizzlipede.name: Sizzlipede
sizzlipede.description: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

centiskorch.name: Centiskorch
centiskorch.description: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

clobbopus.name: Clobbopus
clobbopus.description: It’s very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

grapploct.name: Grapploct
grapploct.description: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

sinistea.name: Sinistea
sinistea.description: The swirl pattern in this Pokémon’s body is its weakness. If it gets stirred, the swirl loses its shape, and Sinistea gets dizzy.

polteageist.name: Polteageist
polteageist.description: Trainers Polteageist trusts will be allowed to experience its distinctive flavor and aroma firsthand by sampling just a tiny bit of its tea.

hatenna.name: Hatenna
hatenna.description: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures’ emotions. If you don’t have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.

hattrem.name: Hattrem
hattrem.description: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.

hatterene.name: Hatterene
hatterene.description: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.

impidimp.name: Impidimp
impidimp.description: Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.

morgrem.name: Morgrem
morgrem.description: When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it’s trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.

grimmsnarl.name: Grimmsnarl
grimmsnarl.description: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.

obstagoon.name: Obstagoon
obstagoon.description: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct.

perrserker.name: Perrserker
perrserker.description: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.

cursola.name: Cursola
cursola.description: Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokémon’s core spirit.

sirfetchd.name: Sirfetch’d
sirfetchd.description: Only Farfetch’d that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon’s leek withers, it will retire from combat.

mrrime.name: Mr. Rime
mrrime.description: It’s highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.

runerigus.name: Runerigus
runerigus.description: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.

milcery.name: Milcery
milcery.description: This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.

alcremie.name: Alcremie
alcremie.description: The moment it evolved, it took on a bitter flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution.

falinks.name: Falinks
falinks.description: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass’s orders are absolute.

pincurchin.name: Pincurchin
pincurchin.description: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.

snom.name: Snom
snom.description: It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.

frosmoth.name: Frosmoth
frosmoth.description: Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies over fields and mountains. The temperature of its wings is less than −290 degrees Fahrenheit.

stonjourner.name: Stonjourner
stonjourner.description: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun’s descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.

eiscue.name: Eiscue
eiscue.description: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.

indeedee.name: Indeedee
indeedee.description: It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. Males will act as valets for those they serve, looking after their every need.

morpeko.name: Morpeko
morpeko.description: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It’s also generating electricity.

cufant.name: Cufant
cufant.description: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It’s also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.

copperajah.name: Copperajah
copperajah.description: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.

dracozolt.name: Dracozolt
dracozolt.description: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.

arctozolt.name: Arctozolt
arctozolt.description: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.

dracovish.name: Dracovish
dracovish.description: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.

arctovish.name: Arctovish
arctovish.description: Though it’s able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.

duraludon.name: Duraludon
duraludon.description: Its body resembles polished metal, and it’s both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

dreepy.name: Dreepy
dreepy.description: After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.

drakloak.name: Drakloak
drakloak.description: It’s capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.

dragapult.name: Dragapult
dragapult.description: When it isn’t battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.

zacian.name: Zacian
zacian.description: Now armed with a weapon it used in ancient times, this Pokémon needs only a single strike to fell even Gigantamax Pokémon.

zamazenta.name: Zamazenta
zamazenta.description: Its ability to deflect any attack led to it being known as the Fighting Master’s Shield. It was feared and respected by all.

eternatus.name: Eternatus
eternatus.description: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.

kubfu.name: Kubfu
kubfu.description: Kubfu trains hard to perfect its moves. The moves it masters will determine which form it takes when it evolves.

urshifu.name: Urshifu
urshifu.description: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.

zarude.name: Zarude
zarude.description: Within dense forests, this Pokémon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It's incredibly aggressive, and the other Pokémon of the forest fear it.

regieleki.name: Regieleki
regieleki.description: This Pokémon is a cluster of electrical energy. It’s said that removing the rings on Regieleki’s body will unleash the Pokémon’s latent power.

regidrago.name: Regidrago
regidrago.description: An academic theory proposes that Regidrago’s arms were once the head of an ancient dragon Pokémon. The theory remains unproven.

glastrier.name: Glastrier
glastrier.description: Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. It’s also a belligerent Pokémon—anything it wants, it takes by force.

spectrier.name: Spectrier
spectrier.description: It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one—it doesn’t use its sense of sight. Spectrier’s kicks are said to separate soul from body.

calyrex.name: Calyrex
calyrex.description: Calyrex is a merciful Pokémon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.

wyrdeer.name: Wyrdeer
wyrdeer.description: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.

kleavor.name: Kleavor
kleavor.description: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokémon in the wilds, one’s only recourse is to flee.

ursaluna.name: Ursaluna
ursaluna.description: I believe it was Hisui’s swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.

basculegion.name: Basculegion
basculegion.description: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui’s rivers is Basculegion’s equal.

sneasler.name: Sneasler
sneasler.description: Because of Sneasler’s virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.

overqwil.name: Overqwil
overqwil.description: Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname “sea fiend.” It slurps up poison to nourish itself.

enamorus.name: Enamorus
enamorus.description: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokémon’s love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.
